  "sourceCode": "Employer Portal",
  "title": "Senior Talent Acquisition Executive (Gaming)",
  "description": "<p><strong>Job Responsibilities</strong></p><ul><li>Manage full recruitment lifecycle for gaming-related roles (e.g., game developers, designers, QA, live ops, art, engineering).</li><li>Source, screen, and engage candidates using targeted strategies (platforms, databases, community channels).</li><li>Coordinate interviews, provide timely feedback, and support hiring managers throughout the process.</li><li>Build and maintain strong talent pipelines for key and niche gaming skill sets.</li><li>Support offer processes, onboarding coordination, and candidate experience handling.</li><li>Track recruitment metrics and provide insights to improve hiring quality.</li><li>Collaborate with HR and business leaders on workforce planning and recruitment priorities.</li><li>Maintain recruitment documentation, trackers, and workflows.</li></ul><p><strong>Job Requirements:</strong></p><ul><li>Bachelor’s degree in Human Resources, Business, or related discipline.</li><li>Minimum 3–5 years of talent acquisition or recruitment experience (preferably with some exposure to gaming, tech, or digital entertainment roles).</li><li>Strong sourcing and stakeholder management skills.</li><li>Excellent communication, coordination, and time-management abilities.</li><li>Ability to work independently in a fast-paced environment and manage multiple hiring priorities.</li><li>Experience with full recruitment process from candidate sourcing through offer and onboarding.</li><li>Familiarity with gaming industry roles and community channels is an advantage (e.g., Discord, GitHub, game dev forums). </li></ul>",
